philipturner/metal-float64 — initial repo skeleton
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

    https://github.com/philipturner/metal-float64
    Copyright (c) 2023 Philip Turner
    Licensed under the MIT License

The initial repo layout (directory structure, CMake package skeleton, the
`sf64_*` C ABI-first shape) was seeded from this project. No source files
from the upstream are carried in the shipped library: every `sf64_*`
implementation — arithmetic, compare, convert, sqrt/fma, rounding,
classify, trig/exp/log/hyp/pow, special functions — is either original
or ported from Mesa / SLEEF / SoftFloat as attributed below.

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Mesa3D — arithmetic / compare / convert / sqrt / fma / rounding
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

    src/compiler/glsl/float64.glsl
    https://gitlab.freedesktop.org/mesa/mesa
    Copyright (c) The Mesa 3D Graphics Library project contributors
    Licensed under the BSD-3-Clause License

    src/compiler/nir/nir_lower_double_ops.c
    https://gitlab.freedesktop.org/mesa/mesa
    Copyright (c) The Mesa 3D Graphics Library project contributors
    Licensed under the MIT License

Algorithms for add/sub/mul/div/rem, sqrt, fma, the full conversion matrix,
and the rounding helpers (rcp, rsqrt, floor/ceil/trunc/rint/etc.) were ported
from these files. Restructured from GLSL to scalar C++ where needed; the
underlying bit-manipulation algorithms are preserved.

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
SLEEF — transcendentals
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

    sleefinline_purec_scalar.h and scalar sources under src/libm/
    https://github.com/shibatch/sleef
    Copyright (c) 2010-2023 Naoki Shibata and contributors
    Licensed under the Boost Software License, Version 1.0

sin/cos/tan, asin/acos/atan/atan2, exp/exp2/exp10/expm1, log/log2/log10/log1p,
sinh/cosh/tanh/asinh/acosh/atanh, pow, cbrt, erf/erfc, tgamma/lgamma, fmod,
remainder. The purec-scalar variant compiles against plain `double` plus
`fma` and `sqrt`, so the SLEEF sources drop straight onto the `sf64_*` ABI.

